  "texts": [
    "The authors have tested this protocol to virtually screen a large molecular library against D4, MT1, and AMPC targets.",
    "They achieved a notable retrieval rate of over 80% for experimentally validated hits while significantly reducing computational expenses by 14 fold.",
    "LBVS is based on selecting, from databases, molecules that share similar structural features with an active ligand.",
    "Pharmacophore-based virtual screening is one of the LBVS techniques.",
    "It involves building 2D fingerprints of one or more active ligands using molecular descriptors such as hydrogen-bond donors, hydrogen-bond acceptors, and aromatic rings."
